Rating: 4
This cake was just wonderful! So easy and a huge hit at my young son's class birthday party! The teachers requested a cake without creme or frosting, so I found this-- using homemade applesauce and adding a simple powdered sugar glaze were the only changes. I have had 3 requests for the recipe! A keeper!

Rating: 3
Execellent when you are trying to lower cholesterol. Tasted quite good. Mine was very light...I used 2 tspns baking powder and no baking soda, 1 cup of maple syrup instead of 1/2 and 1 tspn of cinnamon instead of 1/2 tspn. I used one stick of melted butter...I would have put two in a regular recipe...and I added some chocolate chips and baked it in a heart shaped pan. Looked and tasted lovely and is supporting my reduction of bad cholesterol while still having my cake. Thanks

